contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:08.687 --> 01:09.577
thank you very much.

01:09.578 --> 01:11.103
We are three days grace.

01:11.104 --> 01:12.920
We'll be right back.

01:14.652 --> 01:16.205
When you said that we were going out dancing,

01:16.206 --> 01:18.073
I didn't think this was what you meant.

01:18.074 --> 01:19.239
I--I said there might be dancing.

01:19.240 --> 01:20.385
Your exact words were,

01:20.386 --> 01:22.542
"I cannot wait to get you out on the dance floor."

01:22.543 --> 01:24.649
Come on. Jumping up and down can be dancing.

01:24.650 --> 01:26.208
Another round, folks?

01:26.209 --> 01:27.104
Yeah, yeah.

01:27.105 --> 01:28.341
2 would be great.

01:28.342 --> 01:29.095
Brandon!

01:29.096 --> 01:30.918
Order up for the band.

01:31.598 --> 01:33.928
Sorry, guys.Give me one sec.

01:35.869 --> 01:37.333
Does that guy look familiar to you?

01:37.334 --> 01:38.192
I don't think so.

01:38.193 --> 01:38.980
You?

01:38.981 --> 01:40.070
I don't know.

01:40.071 --> 01:41.411
Why don't you play, man?

01:45.720 --> 01:46.848
-- You gotta play.
-- no no no

01:46.977 --> 01:50.051
Here, I got a guitar--I got a guitar right here.

01:56.802 --> 01:58.002
Freebird!

02:11.959 --> 02:13.497
He's amazing.

02:14.574 --> 02:15.829
Oh, wait a minute.

02:15.830 --> 02:16.906
That's why I know this guy.

02:16.907 --> 02:18.454
He used to play for crimson doves.

02:18.455 --> 02:19.462
-- Who?
-- Crimson doves.

02:19.463 --> 02:20.585
They were a local band,

02:20.586 --> 02:22.154
uh...big favorite.

02:22.155 --> 02:23.743
They released this great album a few years back,

02:23.744 --> 02:25.754
and then they just kinda disappeared.

02:29.979 --> 02:31.632
Do you feel that?

02:43.941 --> 02:45.148
Ten.

02:47.984 --> 02:49.296
What?What's going on?

03:11.193 --> 03:12.397
Let me guess.

03:12.793 --> 03:14.758
That wasn't the ghost of jimi hendrix?

03:14.948 --> 03:17.972
But it gave new meaning to stage fright.

